The paper discusses reinforcement learning agents and their optimization of features specified in a reward function, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on robots deployed in environments that humans act in suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm developed in the paper is based on Maximum Causal Entropy IRL, which is a machine learning technique, indicating a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The use of the algorithm to infer preferences for how the environment should be organized suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions proof-of-concept environments, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) in designing and evaluating these environments.
